text:
East 241st Street (extreme left), south side, east from but not including White Plains Road, to and including Furman Ave. The frame house, in the right foreground, bears No. 4640 Garden Place, adjoining the S.E. corner of East 241st Street. Garden Place, a one block street is at this date (1937) no longer in existence. The frame houses in the center face on the east side of Furman Ave. Photographers vantage point is the "L" station at 241st Street and White Plains Road.

May 24, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

original_title: Bronx: Cranford Avenue - White Plains Road
text:
(1)
Cranford Ave., east from White Plains Road. On the left is St. Mary of the Angels Protestant Episcopal Church (Italian), at No. 729, between White Plains Road and Barnes Ave. The 2 ½ -story house on the right bears No. 730.

P. L. Sperr.

May 24, 1928.

(2)
An exclusive view of the church on the north side of the avenue.

May 24, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.
